{{Quote|We're not worried. We think it's a neat plan. We bet it can't fail.|Bahb on Han's plan of escape on [[Kabray]]|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 95">[[Star Wars (1977) 95|''Star Wars'' (1977) 95]]</ref>}}
'''Bahb''' was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Zeltron/Legends|Zeltron]], who, along with three other Zeltrons&mdash;[[Jahn]], [[Marruc]] and [[Rahuhl]], volunteered to be attaché to [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]]. Despite Leia's dislike of Zeltrons, [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar]] felt it was essential to assign the boys to her in order to retain diplomatic ties to their homeworld. Bahb and the other Zeltrons were delighted to work with Leia, of whom they'd heard many stories, and well as [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]&mdash;although they initially mistook him for [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]].

==Assignments==
{{Quote|Let's get 'em!|Bahb as he charges after [[Nagai/Legends|Nagai]] warriors|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 95" />}}
Their first assignment was to a [[Skirmish on Kabray|diplomatic party]] on [[Kabray]]. Unfortunately, the [[Nagai/Legends|Nagai]] had targeted the gathering as an opportunity to hamstring the Alliance, and captured the entire party and Leia's newly arrived group. Trapped in a room, the four Zeltrons devised a plan, hoisting Jahn up to the ceiling where he jumped on an incoming Nagai guard. The Zeltrons then turned the tables on the Nagai raiding party, capturing them all and turning their guns on them. Their fierce efforts impressed both Han and Leia, who began to warm up to the Zeltrons. Their efforts were also noticed by the Nagai [[Den Siva|leadership]] who would later target their homeworld.

[[File:Bahb2.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Bahb and [[Rahuhl]] are strangled by a [[Maccabree]] during the [[Second Battle of Endor]].]]

Returning to [[Endor/Legends|Endor]] with their captured prisoners, Bahb and the Zeltrons handed them over for interrogation. They were there when the invading Nagai fleet came out of [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]], and were the first to detect them with Leia. Bahb and Jahn then ran off to find and warn Luke Skywalker in the forest. After warning him and returning to the tracking station to watch the fighter squadrons engaged in space, the four Zeltrons were unexpectedly caught up in a ground battle against a force of [[Maccabree]]s and Nagai who had sneaked onto the [[Moon/Legends|moon's]] surface. After repelling the first warrior, many more arrived, one grabbing Bahb around the neck. Only the timely arrival of Luke Skywalker who discovered the Maccabree's weakness, saved the lives of the Zeltrons. They then evacuated Endor along with the rest of the Alliance.

Having fled Endor, Bahb and the Zeltron boys also took part in the [[Battle of Zeltros]]. The planet had in part been identified as a target due to their efforts on Kabray. During the battle they were captured by the [[Tof/Legends|Tofs]] who mistakenly identified them as important Alliance commanders. They were then imprisoned on the Tof flagship '' [[Merriweather]] ''. Luke Skywalker, teamed up with [[Hoojib/Legends|Hoojibs]] and [[Hiromi]], led a successful mission to rescue them.

